This paper involves the optimization of control systems for connected and automated vehicles, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques for predicting vehicle speed, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization of powertrain control and thermal management also involves the use of optimization and control theory, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of simulation and modeling techniques, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of energy savings, which could potentially fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) if statistical methods were used for analysis.
